29namespace webrtc {
30
31VideoReceiver2::VideoReceiver2(Clock* clock, VCMTiming* timing)
32 : clock_(clock),
33 timing_(timing),
34 decodedFrameCallback_(timing_, clock_),
35 codecDataBase_() {
36 decoder_sequence_checker_.Detach();
37}
38
39VideoReceiver2::~VideoReceiver2() {
40 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&construction_sequence_checker_);
41}
42
43// Register a receive callback. Will be called whenever there is a new frame
44// ready for rendering.
45int32_t VideoReceiver2::RegisterReceiveCallback(
46 VCMReceiveCallback* receiveCallback) {
47 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&construction_sequence_checker_);
48 RTC_DCHECK(!IsDecoderThreadRunning());
49 // This value is set before the decoder thread starts and unset after
50 // the decoder thread has been stopped.
51 decodedFrameCallback_.SetUserReceiveCallback(receiveCallback);
52 return VCM_OK;
53}
54
55// Register an externally defined decoder object. This may be called on either
56// the construction sequence or the decoder sequence to allow for lazy creation
57// of video decoders. If called on the decoder sequence |externalDecoder| cannot
58// be a nullptr. It's the responsibility of the caller to make sure that the
59// access from the two sequences are mutually exclusive.
60void VideoReceiver2::RegisterExternalDecoder(VideoDecoder* externalDecoder,
61 uint8_t payloadType) {
62 if (IsDecoderThreadRunning()) {
63 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&decoder_sequence_checker_);
64 // Don't allow deregistering decoders on the decoder thread.
65 RTC_DCHECK(externalDecoder != nullptr);
66 } else {
67 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&construction_sequence_checker_);
68 }
69
70 if (externalDecoder == nullptr) {
71 codecDataBase_.DeregisterExternalDecoder(payloadType);
72 return;
73 }
74 codecDataBase_.RegisterExternalDecoder(externalDecoder, payloadType);
75}
76
77bool VideoReceiver2::IsExternalDecoderRegistered(uint8_t payloadType) const {
78 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&decoder_sequence_checker_);
79 return codecDataBase_.IsExternalDecoderRegistered(payloadType);
80}
81
82void VideoReceiver2::DecoderThreadStarting() {
83 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&construction_sequence_checker_);
84 RTC_DCHECK(!IsDecoderThreadRunning());
85#if RTC_DCHECK_IS_ON
86 decoder_thread_is_running_ = true;
87#endif
88}
89
90void VideoReceiver2::DecoderThreadStopped() {
91 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&construction_sequence_checker_);
92 RTC_DCHECK(IsDecoderThreadRunning());
93#if RTC_DCHECK_IS_ON
94 decoder_thread_is_running_ = false;
95 decoder_sequence_checker_.Detach();
96#endif
97}
98
99// Must be called from inside the receive side critical section.
100int32_t VideoReceiver2::Decode(const VCMEncodedFrame* frame) {
101 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&decoder_sequence_checker_);
102 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "VideoReceiver2::Decode");
103 // Change decoder if payload type has changed
104 VCMGenericDecoder* decoder =
105 codecDataBase_.GetDecoder(*frame, &decodedFrameCallback_);
106 if (decoder == nullptr) {
107 return VCM_NO_CODEC_REGISTERED;
108 }
109 return decoder->Decode(*frame, clock_->CurrentTime());
110}
111
112// Register possible receive codecs, can be called multiple times
113int32_t VideoReceiver2::RegisterReceiveCodec(uint8_t payload_type,
114 const VideoCodec* receiveCodec,
115 int32_t numberOfCores) {
116 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&construction_sequence_checker_);
117 RTC_DCHECK(!IsDecoderThreadRunning());
118 if (receiveCodec == nullptr) {
119 return VCM_PARAMETER_ERROR;
120 }
121 if (!codecDataBase_.RegisterReceiveCodec(payload_type, receiveCodec,
122 numberOfCores)) {
123 return -1;
124 }
125 return 0;
126}
127
128bool VideoReceiver2::IsDecoderThreadRunning() {
129#if RTC_DCHECK_IS_ON
130 return decoder_thread_is_running_;
131#else
132 return true;
133#endif
134}
